      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes (fatigue fracture, permanent deformation) and to the regulatory submission claims.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the FDA guidance on pedicle screw testing and are directly predictive of in vivo mechanical performance. Their relevance to the COU is established by the regulatory context and published clinical literature."
