    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly bounded to the ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration and the inter-laboratory reproducibility data partially compensates for the single loading condition. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%) are satisfied. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory use of the FEA predictions.",
